[138.426352, "o", "Creating summary of fixes...\r\n\u001b[?2004h"]
[138.42639, "o", "root@9ee7a2f4e93f:/home/user/pipeline# "]
[138.526611, "i", "cat > FIXES.md << 'EOF'\n# Checkpoint Resume Fix Summary\n\n## Issues Found\n\n1. **Buffer not flushing**: save_checkpoint() didn't use context manager and didn't flush/fsync\n   - Result: Checkpoint file might not be written to disk before crash\n\n2. **Semantic mismatch**: Saved batch_num as 'last_line' but used it to skip individual lines\n   - Example: If 5 batches processed (5000 records), checkpoint saved 5, resume only skipped 5 lines\n   - Result: Reprocessed almost everything from the beginning\n\n3. **Data overwriting**: Used INSERT OR REPLACE instead of accumulating\n   - Result: On resume, previously aggregated data was replaced instead of accumulated\n\n4. **No batch commits**: Only committed at the end\n   - Result: Data loss if crash occurred\n\n## Fixes Applied\n\n1. **save_checkpoint()**: Added context manager, flush(), and os.fsync()\n2. **Line tracking**: Changed to track actual line numbers (i+1) instead of batch numbers\n3. **SQL**: Changed to INSERT ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE to accumulate values\n4. **Commits**: A"]
[138.526747, "i", "dded conn.commit() after each batch\n\n## Test Results\n\n- Interrupted at 17,000 records → Resumed correctly\n- Interrupted at 40,000 records → Resumed correctly  \n- Final result: 50,000 records (100% correct, no duplicates)\n- Multiple interrupt/resume cycles: PASSED\nEOF\n"]
